Maryland collected $1 billion in corporate income taxes, the most in the region.
Although they are moving in the same direction, the local tax burden on entrepreneurs is not growing as fast in these three places.
The growth rate in D.C. was at the national average of 4.3%, while Maryland's growth was significantly higher, at 4.9%.
In Virginia only, the tax increase was below average, at 4.1%.
Virginia has the lowest corporate income tax rate of all three districts (all of which have the same taxation), 6%.
Maryland's corporate tax rate is 8.25%, while the D.C. average remains relatively high at 9.975%.
